snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #132
snippet.description: The body of Osama bin Laden was found during an archeological dig next door to the neighbor he loved every Cinco de Mayo with soup.

snippet.title: Coupe du Jour
snippet.description: "Shotgun Etiquette" demands that you refrain from slurping, dipping crackers or wearing a seatbelt. Should any projectiles approach the vehicle, remain calm and focus on pleasant mealtime discussions, such as the weather, cartwheels or the deliciousness of the soup. And don't forget to use the spoon CLOSEST to you in the glove compartment box.

snippet.title: The History of Cinco de Mayo
snippet.description:
A tradition rich with history and purpose, the annual "Drunken Punching of the Forehead" is superseded only by the "Instant Appearance of Alcoholic Beverages" within the culture. Chips and dip are mandatory, as well.

snippet.title: The Girl Next Door
snippet.description: The first time they saw her and her wild, smiling eyes, they could swear they heard music. They weren't wrong; It was a combination of a worn-out Nat King Cole tape and loud explosions, and it was coming from her house.

snippet.title: P Is For Pterodactyle
snippet.description: Peter Dactyle was a young man with a junior archaeologist's kit and a dream. He would take that dream all the way to the top of his profession one day - but not without the help of his deep, crippling psychosis.

snippet.title: Osama Bin Laden's Final Video
snippet.description:
It was when they answered the door as "Pizza Hut" that he knew something was awry. Only Domino's had the sweet pizza-tracker app that let you know just how soon you'd get your piping-hot pie. Besides, there wasn't a Hut for miles in Pakistan. But as he dove for his AK, the door burst open and he realized it was too late - so instead, he celebrated his last moments on Earth with a hearty gulp of Mountain Dew Code Red.

snippet.description: It's a dog's world when a friend dies in a freak pigeon pecking incident, leaving the mourners to cry a tear-a-masooooooo because they still have exams.

snippet.title: Cheater
snippet.description: Coincidentally, a giant glob of spooge was the correct answer to number 12. However, he unwittingly signed his test "Holy Shit, This is the Sweetest Grip" and thus the jig was up.

snippet.title: Big Surprise
snippet.description: Nothing helps wash down the bitter taste of knowing you're capable of ruthless back-alley baby-stopping quite like a heaping slice of homemade Tiramisu.

snippet.title: Professor Pigeon
snippet.description: Pigeons typically don't get tenure. But his discourse on Proust is thrilling to behold.

snippet.title: The Last Words of Troy Hicks
snippet.description: A simple man who enjoyed simple pleasures, Troy loved creating righteous shit for his friend Randall to check out. Until that fateful, flaming, chainsaw-filled day the shit-checking stopped.

snippet.title: It's a Dog's Dog's World
snippet.description: Personally, I kinda like coming up to a line of hydrants and peeing on the one right next to someone. It feels like a team effort that way, instead of feeling like everyone's just in it to selfishly spread around their own scent.

snippet.title: Men's Room
snippet.description: Wilbur and Hank... a chance encounter. 135-second film by 5secondfilm.com.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #130
snippet.description: In an AIDS campaign to raise awareness for abandoned food babies a Vietnam Veteran must smoke his way out of a game show in order to win the most Easter eggs.

snippet.title: Bunny Brothers
snippet.description: Times are tight and rent is rough in the big city, particularly when you've been running out of places to store dead bodies and meth in your tiny downtown artist's loft. So sometimes, drastic measures must be taken, like moving in with your goody-two-shoes, dinner-party-loving brother. It happens.

snippet.title: Guess That Murder
snippet.description: As a runner-up, you go home with a lifetime supply of Turtle Wax, but if you'll notice, the turtle on the bottle has been labeled upside-down as if it's dead on its back. Which is a cute little touch, considering that you are also dead.

snippet.title: Guns A Blazin'
snippet.description: Right before this, he showed the other men in his squad a photograph he kept tucked away in his helmet. "This is what I got waiting for me back home," he said lovingly. It was a picture of him taking a massive rip off a killer 4-footer self serve. It was then that they knew he wasn't going to last long in Uptight Company.

snippet.title: Food Baby
snippet.description: There's a Thursday farmer's market down the street that sells this stuff farm-fresh organic, kale-fed and free-range. Most people just hang around and get free samples without buying any baby, so support your local farmer and pay for a plate sometime.

snippet.title: Unprotected Shootout
snippet.description: Gun AIDS. A little dab'll do ya.

snippet.title: Douchebag a True Story
snippet.description: The history of the Douchebag: a 122-second film by 5secondfilms.com

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #129
snippet.description: The heartbreak of over hearing his ex-girlfriend's moans of pleasure forces Lenny to banish his heart to prison where he can masturbate and drink in peace before exploding with depression when his heart jumps on a grenade.

snippet.title: Forgotten Hero
snippet.description: He was the last of three brothers who all died similarly; Ryan, who took heavy fire at a shooting range on Free Blindfold Day; Jacob, who drowned in his oatmeal at the mess hall; and Peter, felled by the General's spring-loaded prank penknife on April Fool's. Their mother wept openly upon hearing the news, then as she attempted to back out of the driveway and head off to the funeral, drove the car clean through the garage and knocked herself unconscious.

snippet.title: Nobody's Driving
snippet.description: The best part about the cop asking for nobody's license and registration is, it takes forever! And you can just drunkenly slip out the passenger side door and run away while he's waiting for it!

snippet.title: Switch Hitter
snippet.description: Stay gold, Hornyboy. Stay gold.

snippet.title: Lenny's First Day Back From Prison
snippet.description: The memories came rushing back almost as soon as the words escaped his lips. The grooves his fingers made in the prison bars over time. The whip-crack of towels, made entirely out of shivs. The nickname his overlord, The Golfer, gave him on the first day: The 19th Hole.

snippet.title: My Neighbor the Ex-Girlfriend
snippet.description: Her Facebook status reads "In a Relationship Totally Packed With Mind-Blowing Sex, Jon. Remember this vagina? Hope so, because it's the last you'll ever see." An incredibly specific status, to be sure, but one she managed to find in the drop-down menu all the same.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #128
snippet.description: After a wild and drunken party of riding the elevators, a few men fantasize about having children but realize they can only pick up girls from their high towered balcony.

snippet.title: How to Hit on Girls but from Your Balcony
snippet.description: In this anthropological field study, we witness the effect of male attention on unwitting passersby and watch as a strange symbiotic relationship begins. But from a balcony.

snippet.title: What to Expect When You're Expecting
snippet.description: They were so "on board," in fact, that their finger-ticklin' dudeshake went on for a good forty minutes. When they stopped and came to, they were sitting out on the street with all of their stuff in a hasty pile next to them.

snippet.title: Goin' Up?
snippet.description: It's even worse when some little brat steps in with you, hits all the buttons for every floor, and winds up vivisecting the entire structure like that horse in "The Cell."

snippet.title: Collection Day
snippet.description: If you have a totally kick-ass party filled with lots and lots of booze receptacles, and say his name three times in a mirror, he will come.

snippet.title: Bad Times and Broken Roofs
snippet.description: You can't hold Roof Monster down. You can only report him to the police and have your mom mail his sleepover stuff back to his mom while he's in the drunk tank.

Grown men have a serious discussion. A 170-second film by 5secondfilms.com.

snippet.description: In this thrilling installment of the hit series "Hack3r C@t," the team encounters a nasty firewall and has to break through in time to stop a neutron bomb from detonating the town of Silver Spring. They're going to need a lot of luck, and purr-fect timing.

snippet.title: Lady in Red
snippet.description: There's a special VIP section in the burn ward, where the Dom Perignon can be attached to your IV, gift bags full of rare exotic aloe are dispensed, and best of all, only the pretty people get to go.

snippet.title: 2 Clones, Chillin'
snippet.description: Onanism? More like Clonanism! Wait, what?

snippet.title: Nom de Plume
snippet.description: One day, these evil, armless, inanimate objects will realize that their telekinetic abilities could be put to far better use by, say, pulling our guts out through our eye sockets, rather than just holding guns the way we hold them. Let us pray that day never comes.

snippet.title: Sentencing
snippet.description: Justice was harsh and swift - 20 minutes without a chance of parole - but they let him off early for good behavior.

snippet.title: Drugs and Your Teens
snippet.description: The new craze! Teens experiment with dangerous drugs. Knowledge is power! A 135-second film by 5secondfilms!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #126
snippet.description: A terrible gambler locks his keys in his car after a strong drink pushes him over the edge in to hipster hallucinations and SPAM scams.

snippet.title: Request For Urgent Business Relationship
snippet.description: And to think: All he needed was their bank routing number. He was so close. So, so close to giving random people he's never met all the money they could imagine, based on some unspoken rule he has no context for or ability to describe. Food for thought, right?

snippet.title: Hipster Goggles
snippet.description: Turns any lame party into a totally not-lame deconstruction of lameness, filtered through a winking parody of fashion trends, stale Pabst, and detached observations about the outdated, now-meaningless use of the word "hipster!" Also oven mitts.

snippet.title: Strong Drink
snippet.description: To be fair, the patron kept pressing him about a particularly strong drink he made, from a long time ago. The bartender was there to promote his new album "S.A.M.E." (Serving All My Enemies), not talk about the controversial drink. He didn't mean to rip his shirt off and break the glass, but he's just an emotional man with a lot of baggage.

snippet.title: AAA Phone Service
snippet.description: If it's an emergency, they tell you to hang up and dial 911, or barring that, just die.

snippet.title: Rushin' Roulette
snippet.description: Never leave ingenious escape plans up to the one P.O.W. who flunked out of fourth-grade math.

snippet.title: Naked Came the Gorlac
snippet.description: Gorlac and Olivia's relationship is put to the test at a friend's wedding. A 283-second film by 5secondfilms!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #125
snippet.description: A telegram informs a man of his long lost twins vegan needs for animal free-beer on St. Patrick's Day but through hypnosis he will settle for a turkey dinner instead.

snippet.title: Hypnotic Southern General
snippet.description: Photos going back as far as the Battle of Appomattox seem to include him, at least somewhere in the background. They're blurry, but he appears to be hiding something fat, bleeding and tastefully dressed, almost entirely underneath his coat. The look on his face is one of both steely determination and demented purpose.

snippet.title: Not Easy Being Green
snippet.description: He lep-baits his friends at every turn, whether they accidentally speak in limerick or whether they just so happen to buy a box of Lucky Charms. In fact, one time they were all in the car and there was a rainbow, and they all just looked away or fiddled with the radio, which only made it worse.
